      "day": "2026-07-21",
      "start": "09:00",
      "duration": "04:00",
      "abstract": "**\"Users with extended rights\"** (admins, checkusers, arbitrators, stewards, bureaucrats, oversighters etc.) - are a central component of  Wikimedia communities: the front line of protecting and sustaining Wikimedia projects. Being elected by their communities, they hold community trust and support the safety of the communities and the reliability of the content.\r\nLast year at Wikimania we organized the first ever global convening of users with extended rights. This year we are inviting users for a second edition.\r\nThis event will be a place for users to connect with one another, exchange experiences across wikis, brainstorm solutions to problems, discuss areas of emphasis for new collaborative work, to build capacity by learning from each other, and to create a network for support into the future. Topics will include safety, privacy, policy tooling, and cross-wiki experience exchange. The program will be co-created with users with extended rights themselves, making sure that the event will be meaningful for this group.\r\n\r\n<br>",
