      "abstract": "Gender equity sessions focusing on empowerment, strategy, and content gaps.",
      "recorded": true,
      "url": "https://wikimedia.eventyay.com/wm/wikimania2026/talk/BJT7C7/",
      "speakers": [
        {
          "name": "Rosie Stephenson-Goodknight",
          "bio": "Rosie Stephenson-Goodknight (user:Rosiestep) is a Wikipedia editor and administrator, known for her role in addressing gender bias within the Wikimedia movement by significantly increasing the quantity and quality of women's biographies. A prolific contributor since 2007, she co-founded Wiki Women in Red, WikiWomen\\*Summit x Wikimania, WikiConference North America, and WikiWomen’s User Group. Women in Red was shortlisted for the ITU/UN Women GEM-TECH award (2016). Since 2017, she has served as the Wikipedia Visiting Scholar at Northeastern University, focusing on historical women writers. She has conducted Wiki movement research projects related to Wikidata Wikipedia content, as well as movement leaders. Rosie served as AffCom member and Chair (2016-2021); Board member and Vice-President of Wikimedia D.C. (2016-2021); and a member of the Wikimedia Foundation Board of Trustees (2021-2024). In 2025, she joined WikiPortraits as a literary festival photographer. In recognition of her impact, Rosie was honored as Wikipedian of the Year (2016) and was knighted in part for her Wikipedia work (2018). She is currently writing a historical Western trilogy in a neo-dime novel format. She makes her home in California, USA.",
          "url": "https://wikimedia.eventyay.com/wm/wikimania2026/speakers/HAF7EQ/"
        }
      ],
      "day_label": "Tue 21 Jul"
