      "room": "Agora 🌐",
      "day": "2026-07-24",
      "start": "09:30",
      "duration": "00:55",
      "abstract": "Wikimedia volunteers publish community newspapers, such as German Wikipedia's *Kurier*, English Wikipedia's *The Signpost,* French Wikipedia's *RAW,* French Wiktionary's *Actualités*.\r\n\r\nBesides these, Wikimedians present numerous newsletters to alert interest groups of project developments, community accomplishments, available shared resources, and to raise attention to social and ethical issues. Examples of popular newsletters include updates from Wikidata and Outreach.\r\n\r\nThis workshop will include brief presentations from regular contributors to Wikimedia newspapers and newsletters, then engage attendees to contribute their own news for publication. Could be existing ones or to build a new one, like for Wikisource for example.\r\n\r\nOptions for contributing will include writing community notices for publications to share, starting the submission process to get editorial review for longer articles which you may wish to develop, or just talking with editors and contributors of publications who may be in the room.\r\n\r\nYour favorite community publications will be at this workshop! Also, you are a journalist, and you have freedom to share information as Wikipedia community news, or elsewhere in Wikimedia projects. Editing Wikipedia is not a crime!",
      "recorded": true,
      "url": "https://wikimedia.eventyay.com/wm/wikimania2026/talk/GLEQ39/",
      "speakers": [
        {
          "name": "Der-Wir-Ing",
          "bio": "Mostly active in German wikipedia, but also on global level https://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/Special:CentralAuth/Der-Wir-Ing",
          "url": "https://wikimedia.eventyay.com/wm/wikimania2026/speakers/YWGLCD/"
        },
        {
          "name": "Lane Rasberry",
          "bio": "Lane Rasberry is Wikimedian-in-residence at the [School of Data Science](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/School_of_Data_Science \"School of Data Science\") at the University of Virginia. His interests include [popular science](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Popular_science \"Popular science\"), [consumer protection](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Consumer_protection \"Consumer protection\"), [civic engagement](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Civic_engagement \"Civic engagement\"), access to health information, [clinical research](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clinical_research \"Clinical research\"), the Open Movement, [data science](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Data_science \"Data science\"), [LGBT history](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LGBT_history \"LGBT history\"), and [Wikimedia projects](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikimedia_projects \"Wikimedia projects\").",
          "url": "https://wikimedia.eventyay.com/wm/wikimania2026/speakers/KMUCFU/"
        },
        {
          "name": "Noé",
          "bio": "Wiktionarian, WikiTinker, WikiBard, WikiMuse. My home project is French Wiktionary. I write guidelines, documentation and help pages, I publish French Wiktionary monthly newsletter Actualités, I suggest editorial incentives.",
          "url": "https://wikimedia.eventyay.com/wm/wikimania2026/speakers/XCVAV8/"
        }
      ],
      "day_label": "Fri 24 Jul"
