      "start": "13:30",
      "duration": "00:55",
      "abstract": "[Lingua Libre](https://lingualibre.org/wiki/LinguaLibre:Main_Page) is a recording tool that allows any registered user to record words in the language of their choosing. The goal is to document language and pronunciation diversity. Recordings are uploaded to wikimedia commons and reused on wiktionaries (automatically for the languages that have a bot version, and manually for others). Lingua Libre has about 1.5 million recordings in more than 330 languages. But some of those languages only have 10 words documented. \r\n\r\nAt Wikimania we'd like to set up a studio where people can drop in and record words in their own language. This aim to document as many new languages as possible, and boost corpus for languages that do not have many recordings yet. Since Wikimania attracts wikimedians from over 100 different countries we hope to get an astounding number of new languages and words !\r\n\r\nSpecifics and opening times to be determined with the program committee. The booth will be manned by volunteers, not by me. We would need a small room.",
