          "name": "Islahaddow",
          "bio": "Isla studied fine art at university and is completing her Master's in African Studies and Media at the University of Cape Town. The common thread woven through her professional life is a single-minded dedication to showcasing the creative voices of Africa’s artists, filmmakers, broadcasters, photographers, poets, writers, and musicians. In 2011, her increasing investment in Africa’s creative and cultural voice and her curiosity about the open movement coincided with working on the WikiAfrica project and joining as a Wikimedian. In 2016, with Florence Devouard and Iolanda Pensa, she formalised these projects under the Wiki In Africa banner. It has been an incredible ride ever since then. Isla also works as the Communications Director for Open Education Global (OEGlobal).",
